  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening National Capacity to Address the Environmental Impacts of Humanitarian Responses to Population Displacement in Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to support Nigeria in implementing environmental management measures that address the environmental consequences of mass displacement and irregular migration, and of the humanitarian response to those population movements. The project aims at systematically and collaboratively integrating environmental considerations in humanitarianhuman mobility policy and planning processes by: i) building knowledge of stakeholders on environmental consequences of crises, mass displacement and humanitarian action; and ii) strengthening the capacityof countries to address such consequences through context-specific analysis, adoption of tools for environmental screening of projects, adoption of coordination mechanisms, and support for the development of relevant policies at various levels.</narrative>
  </description>
